# API

api> /issue

## Idempotency

There may be situations where the same issue request is sent multiple times, for example due to retries after experiencing a network failure or timeout. Identical requests using the same `jti` will return the same `idx` and `uri` as the original successful request during a limited window. Due to this window the must and should not be used as a method for querying existing statuses.

Unique `jti` values must be used for each new status you wish to issue.

If you send a request with a previously used `jti` but a different `statusExpiry`, the service will return a `400 BAD_REQUEST` error. You must generate a new `jti` for the new request.

If two requests with the same `iss` and `jti` arrive at exactly the same time, the service will return a `409 CONFLICT` error for the second request. Retry after a short delay.
